      "body" : "@saurabheights The question was not about a correct regex, but rather why there was a an <code>ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException</code>. That said, you are incorrect: You don&#39;t need to know where the last dot is; you just need the right regex: <code>filename.split(&quot;\\\\.(?=[^.]*$)&quot;)</code>. This uses a <i>look ahead</i> to assert there are no dots anywhere in the input that follows the matching dot."
