  "title" : "Java string split with &quot;.&quot; (dot)",
  "body" : "<p>Why does the second line of this code throw <code>ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException</code>?</p>\n\n<pre><code>String filename = \"D:/some folder/001.docx\";\nString extensionRemoved = filename.split(\".\")[0];\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>While this works:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String driveLetter = filename.split(\"/\")[0];\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I use Java 7.</p>\n"
